<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <br>
If what you are saying is all true then there is no role at all in VI's plan for warriors. <br>
</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Yeah, cos clearly you haven't understood any of the points made.<br>
<br>
No class should have a dominance over a single role in the game.  That is a broken mechanic if it is allowed.  For some *unfathomable* reason, Verant allowed this to persist (and still do) with Cleric healing.  But for every other skill and ability there is choice.<br>
<br>
Monks provide an easier path to tanking well.<br>
Monks provide marginally better tanking where their AC is either so high compared to the mob that it is fully mitigated (pre-XP Change &quot;XP mobs&quot;) or so low than no AC achievable can mitigated the mob (Bosses).<br>
<br>
Warriors provide an ability to maintain a CHeal chain on harder hitting mobs (more HP means you can sustain a mob with 8k damage per round instead of 7k)<br>
Warriors provide a safety net (again due to HP advantage) to cover poor play, lag, whatever.<br>
Warriors have superior taunt mechanisms beyond simple damage.<br>
<br>
The problem is that Warriors should also have the ability to do the physical tanking better on higher level mobs where only their AC can begin to mitigate.  This doesn't work in the current game mechanic because Verant never bothered to balance the Velious and beyond encounters.<br>
<br>
Instead of balancing the ATK (or level or however the mechanic specifically works - we are speculating here, but it is probably Mob ATK) for various ranges of AC as happens for lower level mobs, Verant seem to have just gone &quot;make em all 3k ATK&quot; and that's the problem.  Not enough mobs show a benefit from AC between 1200 and 1800 (or whatever the current max attainable is).<br>
<br>
This *has* already shown signs of change - Cazic Thule 2 has *50s* mobs where ACs beyond 1250 are pretty useful (not really done much to determine the upper limit but I'd expect it fades about 1450 or 1500 for full mitigation).<br>
<br>
I think that Planes of Power will show more of the Cazic Thule 2 design and less of the Luclin &quot;just make em all 3k ATK&quot; approach.  That *alone* will fix Warriors.<br>
<br>
But Verant, being Verant, might need prodded.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
